  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 10:57am.  Clerk - CRHI. 
Defendant Marc A Smith in court with attorney Thomas J Laitsch.  Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Victim rights compliance verified. 
Court reviews case history, status and filings. 
Recommendations presented by Counsel.

Count #1 - The Court orders:
-  $443 ($243 costs and $200 DNA) on a pay plan of $50 per month starting 6/13/16.  Failure to pay as ordered will result in 8 days jail consecutive with Huber. 
-  90 days jail with Work Release/Huber commencing 6/13/16 by 6am.  The Def. is ordered to report and serve the sentence and/or sentence for failure to pay with absolute sobriety and without illegal drugs in his system; failure to comply will result in loss of huber/work release without further process.

Count #2 - 
The Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on probation for 12 months, concurrent and with conditions.  The defendant has no credit for time served.
CONDITIONS:
-  $243 costs on each count. 
-  $200 DNA surcharge on each count. 
-  $142 subpoena fees 
-  AODA assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment per the Agent. 
-  Sex offender evaluation and follow through per the Agent. 
-  Any other assessment, treatment or counseling per the Agent. 
-  Attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or educational program per the Agent. 
-  No contact with JMW (DOB - 10/23/01) or MJW (DOB - 2/2/06)
-  No unsupervised contact with any minor female except the defendant's biological children. 
-  No contact with Megan Baker unless she requests contact.  

The Court finds that a DNA sample has already been taken.
